<paragraph id="902B555AFFD3FFA5AFF9FD98FE76C4D8" blockId="83.[191,1442,622,991]" pageId="83" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis id="A2E08948FFD3FFA5AFF9FD98FEE4C58F" bold="true" box="[192,321,622,648]" pageId="83" pageNumber="82">Definition.</emphasis>
A genus in the clade with 
<taxonomicName id="57942ED9FFD3FFA5ADBEFD99FC65C58E" authority="Hubner, [1831]" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1831" box="[647,960,622,649]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Lychnuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="83" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A2E08948FFD3FFA5ADBEFD99FCA2C58E" box="[647,775,623,649]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="82">Lychnuchus</emphasis>
Hübner, [1831]
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="4F2FEBF8FFD3FFA5ACEAFD99FBA0C58E" box="[979,1029,623,649]" pageId="83" pageNumber="82">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="57942ED9FFD3FFA5AB53FD99FEAEC5AC" authority="Hubner, [1831]" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1831" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Lychnuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="83" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olenus">
<emphasis id="A2E08948FFD3FFA5AB53FD99FA9FC58E" box="[1130,1338,623,649]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="82">Lychnuchus olenus</emphasis>
Hübner, [1831]
</taxonomicName>
, which is a junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="57942ED9FFD3FFA5ADE0FD64FB97C5AC" authority="Fabricius, 1793" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1793" box="[729,1074,657,683]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Hesperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="83" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="celsus">
<emphasis id="A2E08948FFD3FFA5ADE0FD64FCDBC5AC" box="[729,894,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="82">Hesperia celsus</emphasis>
Fabricius, 1793
</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName id="57942ED9FFD3FFA5AB7CFD64FA8FC5AC" authority="Godman, 1901" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1901" box="[1093,1322,657,683]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Dion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="83" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A2E08948FFD3FFA5AB7CFD64FBD9C5AC" box="[1093,1148,658,683]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="82">Dion</emphasis>
Godman, 1901
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="4F2FEBF8FFD3FFA5AA01FD67FACFC5AC" box="[1336,1386,657,683]" pageId="83" pageNumber="82">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="57942ED9FFD3FFA5AFCBFD42FDF9C5CA" authority="Butler, 1872" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1872" box="[242,604,691,718]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Carystus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="83" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gemmatus">
<emphasis id="A2E08948FFD3FFA5AFCBFD42FE6FC5CA" box="[242,458,692,718]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="82">Carystus gemmatus</emphasis>
Butler, 1872
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="57942ED9FFD3FFA5AD99FD45FC1EC5CA" authority="Godman, 1900" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" box="[672,955,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Eutychide" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="83" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A2E08948FFD3FFA5AD99FD45FCA9C5CA" box="[672,780,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="82">Eutychide</emphasis>
Godman, 1900
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="4F2FEBF8FFD3FFA5ACF3FD45FC59C5CA" box="[970,1020,691,717]" pageId="83" pageNumber="82">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="57942ED9FFD3FFA5AB64FD42FF5FC5F7" authority="Hewitson, 1866" authorityName="Hewitson" authorityYear="1866" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Hesperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="83" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="physcella">
<emphasis id="A2E08948FFD3FFA5AB64FD42FA82C5CA" box="[1117,1319,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="82">Hesperia physcella</emphasis>
Hewitson, 1866
</taxonomicName>
) among others (
<figureCitation id="08AF49DFFFD3FFA5AE95FD23FE5EC5F7" box="[428,507,725,752]" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="81.[192,268,1568,1594]" captionTargetBox="[195,1436,217,1533]" captionTargetId="figure-154@81.[192,1440,213,1538]" captionTargetPageId="81" captionText="Figure 15. Genomic tree of Moncina, part 3. See Fig. 1 legend for notations." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392090/files/figure.png" pageId="83" pageNumber="82">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). Keys to J.32.6, or K.2.5, or K. 
<quantity id="576CF8BFFFD3FFA5AC7CFD20FC37C5E8" box="[837,914,725,752]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.04394" pageId="83" pageNumber="82" unit="in" value="4.11">4.11 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="F40528ABFFD3FFA5ACAEFD20FB8CC5F7" author="Evans WH" box="[919,1065,725,752]" pageId="83" pageNumber="82" pagination="54 - 88" refId="ref85135" refString="Evans WH. 1955. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part IV. Hesperiinae and Megathyminae. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 499 p., pl. 54 - 88." type="book chapter" year="1955">Evans (1955)</bibRefCitation>
. Morphologically diverse genus of dark 
<taxonomicName id="57942ED9FFD3FFA5AFCEFD0EFEFEC415" authorityName="A. Warren" authorityYear="2008" box="[247,347,760,786]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="83" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Moncina">Moncina</taxonomicName>
species, unified by a peculiar mitten-shaped valva with a style of varying length and thickness from the ampulla projecting dorsal (a thumb) and harpe projecting caudad, slightly upturned (hand). Other characters include uncus either short and broad, with small or without arms, or long and undivided, beak-like; saccus half of valva in length; either with brands (no brand over vein CuA 
<subScript id="0C10571FFFD3FFA5AC69FC9BFCFDC47C" attach="right" box="[848,856,877,891]" fontSize="6" pageId="83" pageNumber="82">2</subScript>
, long brands under vein CuA 
<subScript id="0C10571FFFD3FFA5ABA4FC9BFB00C47C" attach="left" box="[1181,1189,877,891]" fontSize="6" pageId="83" pageNumber="82">2</subScript>
and over vein 1A+2A) or long prominent stigma reaching vein 1A+2A; 3 
<superScript id="67E1F812FFD3FFA5ADC0FC72FCA2C495" attach="left" box="[761,775,900,914]" fontSize="6" pageId="83" pageNumber="82">rd</superScript>
segment of palpi short. In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly3277.16.1:G904A, aly666.36.3:G181A, aly666.36.3:G182A, aly7193.1.1:T163C, and aly2041.19.7:G130T.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D88E06D1FFD3FFA5AFF9FC06FD55C387" pageId="83" pageNumber="82" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="902B555AFFD3FFA5AFF9FC06FA2AC30E" blockId="83.[192,1423,1007,1034]" box="[192,1423,1007,1034]" pageId="83" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis id="A2E08948FFD3FFA5AFF9FC06FEE1C30D" bold="true" box="[192,324,1008,1034]" pageId="83" pageNumber="82">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is a masculine noun in the nominative singular, given for the mitten-like shape of valva.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="902B555AFFD3FFA5AFF9FBEFFEFCC351" blockId="83.[192,1440,1049,1110]" pageId="83" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis id="A2E08948FFD3FFA5AFF9FBEFFE2BC334" bold="true" box="[192,398,1049,1075]" pageId="83" pageNumber="82">Species included.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="4F2FEBF8FFD3FFA5AEF0FBECFE5FC333" box="[457,506,1050,1076]" pageId="83" pageNumber="82">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName id="57942ED9FFD3FFA5AD58FBECFC57C333" authority="Hayward, 1940" authorityName="Hayward" authorityYear="1940" box="[609,1010,1050,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Lerodea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="83" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gemignanii">
<emphasis id="A2E08948FFD3FFA5AD58FBECFC98C334" box="[609,829,1050,1076]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="82">Lerodea gemignanii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F40528ABFFD3FFA5AC7FFBECFC57C333" author="Hayward KJ" box="[838,1010,1050,1076]" pageId="83" pageNumber="82" pagination="861 - 877" refId="ref85437" refString="Hayward KJ. 1940. New species of Neotropical Hesperiidae from Ecuador (Lep.). Revista de Entomologia (Rio de Janeiro) 11 (3): 861 - 877." type="journal article" year="1940">Hayward, 1940</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="57942ED9FFD3FFA5AB17FBECFEF1C351" authority="Mielke and Casagrande, 2002" authorityName="Mielke and Casagrande" authorityYear="2002" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Enosis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="83" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schausi">
<emphasis id="A2E08948FFD3FFA5AB17FBECFB68C333" box="[1070,1229,1050,1076]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="82">Enosis schausi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F40528ABFFD3FFA5ABEFFBECFEF1C351" author="Mielke OHH &amp; Casagrande MM" pageId="83" pageNumber="82" pagination="27 - 76" refId="ref86606" refString="Mielke OHH, Casagrande MM. 2002. Notas taxonomicas em Hesperiidae neotropicais, com descricoes de novos taxa (Lepidoptera). Revista brasileira de Zoologia 19 (Suplemento 1): 27 - 76." type="journal article" year="2002">Mielke and Casagrande, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="902B555AFFD3FFA5AFF9FB90FD55C387" blockId="83.[192,752,1126,1153]" box="[192,752,1126,1153]" pageId="83" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis id="A2E08948FFD3FFA5AFF9FB90FEF8C387" bold="true" box="[192,349,1126,1152]" pageId="83" pageNumber="82">Parent taxon.</emphasis>
Subtribe 
<taxonomicName id="57942ED9FFD3FFA5AEF1FB90FD48C387" authority="A. Warren, 2008" authorityName="A. Warren" authorityYear="2008" box="[456,749,1126,1153]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="83" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Moncina">
Moncina A. 
<bibRefCitation id="F40528ABFFD3FFA5AD6AFB91FD48C387" author="Warren AD &amp; Ogawa JR &amp; Brower AVZ" box="[595,749,1126,1153]" pageId="83" pageNumber="82" pagination="642 - 676" refId="ref87616" refString="Warren AD, Ogawa JR, Brower AVZ. 2008. Phylogenetic relationships of subfamilies and circumscription of tribes in the family Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera: Hesperioidea). Cladistics 24 (5): 642 - 676." type="journal article" year="2008">Warren, 2008</bibRefCitation>
